  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Diagonal ear lobe crease and microcirculatory disorder in the conjunctiva are both non
      invasive methods documented in the literature as early signs of coronary artery disease.  We
      wish to study the sensitivity and specificity of both signs by conducting a single blind
      study involving patients with documented presence or absence of coronary artery disease via
      angiogram.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
